newspaper_data.title: Sunset Plaza
newspaper_data.entry: On July 29, 1969, the second Sunset Plaza Art and Fashion Promenade held in Sunset Plaza (whose shopping mall is located at 8623 Sunset Boulevard, but also includes businesses spanning from 8589 to 8720 Sunset Boulevard) ended. This festival showcased the artistic and creative talents of the boutiques, shops, and art galleries along and near the Plaza.

newspaper_data.title: It's the Hottest Strip on Sunset
newspaper_data.entry: On July 4, 1990, the Los Angeles Times described the businesses and people along Sunset Plaza (whose shopping mall is located on 8623 Sunset Boulevard), loosely defined as including businesses ranging from the Le Dome restaurant (8720 Sunset Boulevard) to the Sunset Travel agency (8589 Sunset Boulevard). When Chin Chin (8618 Sunset Boulevard), an Asian restaurant, opened up on Sunset Plaza in 1983, this part of Sunset Strip became a trendy place to be, where a “sophisticated, affluent clientele with ties to the entertainment industry and strong fashion convictions” came to shop, dine, and enjoy service at Sunset Plaza. The businesses of Sunset Plaza have a ritzy, classy aura that set them apart from other parts of the Strip.
